parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition coils can cause misfires, engine stalling, and decreased engine performance, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
The failure of the Lysholm supercharger seal can cause oil leaks, engine damage, and decreased engine performance, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Blue smoke emission from the exhaust pipe

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The stalling of the engine can cause accidents, especially at high speeds, and leave the driver stranded.
The design of the engine can cause ignition coil failure, Lysholm supercharger seal failure, and engine stalling, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: blue smoke emission from the exhaust pipe

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The fuel system malfunction can cause the vehicle to emit gas fumes, which can lead to a fire hazard, and also cause the engine to stall or lose power, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: engine stalling or loss of power
bucking or jerking of the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The accelerator pedal sticking can cause the vehicle to accelerate unexpectedly, leading to loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents.
The transmission failure can cause rapid deceleration, leading to loss of control and potential accidents.
symptoms: causing a quick decrease in operating speed
and the "HOLD" light flashes until the car is brought to a complete stop.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the shifter lever lock can cause the car to shift out of park without stepping on the brake, leading to unintended vehicle movement and potential accidents.
symptoms: The keys get jammed in the ignition
and the car can shift out of park without stepping on the brake.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the door lock actuator can cause doors to become inoperable, trapping occupants inside the vehicle, which can lead to safety risks, especially in emergency situations.
symptoms: Doors will not unlock or open from inside or outside
doors can only be opened by manually holding the unlock button and pulling on the door handle

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the belt pulley tensioner can cause the serpentine belt to fall off while driving, leading to engine damage, overheating, and potentially causing accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The serpentine belt falls off while driving
the vehicle is difficult to drive or loses power.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Traction Control System (TCS) and Check Engine Light Issues
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the TCS and Check Engine Light systems can cause serious driveability problems, making the vehicle difficult to control and increasing the risk of accidents, especially in heavy traffic situations.
symptoms: The TCS and Check Engine Light appear on the dashboard
the vehicle has serious driveability problems
the vehicle is difficult to drive in traffic situations
the vehicle loses power or has reduced performance.
